records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jeffrey Dewayne Armstrong in court with attorney Joseph Edward Schubert.  Jennifer Lynn Williams appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case recalled. Sentencing hearing continued. Email from the victim received and filed. Statements made as to sentencing. Court finds the State has complied with victims rights legislation. 

COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction concurrent to COUNT 2 amended and COUNT 3 amended, consecutive to COUNT 4; Court will allow work release; credit for 29 days time served.

COUNT 2 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction concurrent to COUNT 1 amended and COUNT 3 amended, consecutive to COUNT 4; Court will allow work release; credit for 29 days time served.

COUNT 3 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction concurrent to COUNT 1 amended and COUNT 2 amended, consecutive to COUNT 4; Court will allow work release; credit for 29 days time served.

COUNT 4-
Court ordered defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction, consecutive to COUNTS 1, 2 & 3; Court will allow work release;

If revoked, court costs, fees and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b).

Court STAYED the sentence on all counts and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS with the following conditions:

1) Court ordered 60 days of condition time in the House of Correction which is STAYED to be used at the agents discretion. If employed when ordered to serve condition time, defendant is allowed work release;
2) Comply with all Childrens Court orders;
3) No contact with the victim H.L.A. outside of a therapeutic setting. Defendant may have contact in therapeutic setting only with consent of therapist and H.L.A.;
4) Obtain/comply with sex offender treatment and counseling;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety;
6) Provide agent with a list of prescriptions. Any new prescriptions must be provided to agent BEFORE filling them;
7) No unsupervised contact with any children under the age of 16 years. Any conditions of  unsupervised contact with biological children is to be followed pursuant to Childrens Court order;
8) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
9) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay DNA surcharge on COUNT 1 amended only. Court WAIVED DNA surcharge on counts 2 and 3 as amended and count 4 as they are part of a continuous series of events;

Court ordered bail on deposit be applied to costs, fees and surcharges. 

If defendant is revoked and is employed at the time of revocation, Court will allow work release. Defendant may also be considered for the Day Reporting Center and any job training programs within the institution.

Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
